<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101247864337831></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101247864337831><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=5179&mid=101247864337831>RE: ...LOADING</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=5179&mid=101247864337831#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=121232><span id= >Fluxus</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>62 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jan 31st 8:05 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I know drawing aggro is a controversial subject, and everybody agrees that a lot of damage gets a lot of aggro.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, the number of hits also draws aggro.  I think it is a smaller factor than overall damage, but from my experience the number of hits will definitely draw aggro... even when hitting for super-small amounts of damage.  My rogue, when equiped with higher ratio, lower damage weapons will pull aggro even faster than my higher damage, lower aggro weapons.  I'd love to see other rogues comment on this subject.  I'm not saying I'm 100% correct on this issue, as there could be other factors playing into my low-delay gaining-aggro experiences... just adding my observations.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
